The paper deals with multiple access channels (MACs) with bursty user traffic, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of a relay is a common technique in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of physical perturbations on the transmission patterns, which is related to system dynamics and control (cs.SY). The use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) technology is also mentioned, which is a topic in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Lastly, the paper discusses the issue of collision-free performances, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
